      • readWithLength

        public static java.lang.String readWithLength(java.io.DataInput accessor,
                                              int bytesCountLimit)
                                       throws java.io.IOException
        Reads a String in the given Accessor that has been encoded in UTF-8 and with its length. The encoding is as following:

        <length><string>

        Where <length> is the length of <string>. Empty or null lines can also be read.

        Note that carriage returns do not effect the encoding.
        Parameters:
        accessor - Accessor to read
        bytesCountLimit - Maximum accepted length to read
        Returns:
        The read String
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • sendWithLength

        public static void sendWithLength(java.io.DataOutput accessor,
                                  java.lang.String line)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Sends a String in the given Accessor with its length. The encoding is as following:

        <length><string>

        Where <length> is the length of <string>. Empty null lines can also be written.

        Note that carriage returns do not effect the encoding.
        Parameters:
        accessor - Accessor to write
        line - String to send
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • readListWithLength

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> readListWithLength(Accessor accessor,
                                                                  int listSizeLimit,
                                                                  int stringLengthLimit)
                                                           throws java.io.IOException
        Reads a list of String that has been encoded with its length in the given Accessor.
        Empty and null list can also be read.
        Parameters:
        accessor - Accessor to read
        listSizeLimit - Maximum accepted number of elements in the list to read
        stringLengthLimit - Maximum accepted length of String to read
        Returns:
        The read list
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
